{{coord|37|38|11|N|121|54|16|W|region:US|display=title}} {{Infobox park | name = Augustin Bernal Community Park | image = Image:Augustin Bernal Park Pond.jpg | image_size = 300 px | image_alt = | image_caption = Pond in Augustin Bernal Park | map = <!-- or | map_image = --> | map_width = | type = | location = Alameda County, California | nearest_city = Pleasanton, California | coordinates = | area = {{convert|237|acre|km2}} | created = 1971 | operator = Pleasanton, California | visitation_num = | status = | designation = | open = }}
'''Augustin Bernal Community Park''' is a {{convert|237|acre|km2|sing=on}} park in the hills southwest of [[Pleasanton, California]].<ref name="wcpcusrpat">{{cite web |url=http://www.ci.pleasanton.ca.us/services/recreation/rec-augustinpark.html |title=Augustin Bernal Park |accessdate=2011-02-06 |date= |work= |publisher=City of Pleasanton |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719232109/http://www.ci.pleasanton.ca.us/services/recreation/rec-augustinpark.html |archivedate=2011-07-19 |df= }}</ref>
The park was donated to the city in 1971 by [[Walter S. Johnson]],{{efn|Walter S. Johnson was a philanthropist who was noted for his financial support for the restoration of San Francisco's [[Palace of Fine Arts]]. The park is now owned and operated by the City of Pleasanton.<ref name = "Bernal map">[http://www.cityofpleasantonca.gov/pdf/AugustinBernalMap.pdf "Augustin Bernal Community Park Trail Map." City of Pleasanton.] Accessed September 9, 2017</ref>}} and connects to [[Pleasanton Ridge]] Regional Park. The park is named for Spanish settler, Augustin Bernal,to whom the land on which the park sits, was originally granted.<ref name = "Bernal map"/>
Access to the park's public staging area is through a [[gated community]], Golden Eagle Farms. Pleasanton residents can show proof of residency to get past the community's gate at Golden Eagle Way and Foothill Road; non-residents can obtain a one-week permit at Pleasanton's Department of Parks and Community Services.<ref name="wcpcusrpat"/> The Community Services office is at 200 Old Bernal Ave. in Pleasanton.<ref name ="Trailstompers">[http://www.trailstompers.com/pleasanton-ridge-regional-park-and-augustin-bernal-community-park-trail-runs.html "Pleasanton Ridge Regional Park (and Augustin Bernal Community Park). Trailstompers.] Accessed September 11, 2017.</ref>
