{{Use Australian English|date=December 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} [[File:Elephant Rocks - William Bay NP - Dec 2009.jpg|thumb|Elephant Rocks]]
'''Elephant Rocks''' is a sheltered beach in Western Australia, a few hundred metres east of [[Greens Pool]]. It is located about 15&nbsp;km west from Denmark, in [[William Bay National Park]].<ref>http://www.dec.wa.gov.au/component/option,com_hotproperty/task,view/id,98/Itemid,1584/ DEC</ref> Its name is derived from a series of exposed rocks, which from several angles resembles a herd of elephants.<ref>http://www.denmark.com.au/en/Natural+Wonders+of+Denmark/William+Bay+National+Park.htm Denmark Visitor Centre</ref>
;Fact sheet * Location: William Bay National Park * Directions: 15&nbsp;km west of Denmark on South Coast Highway, heading towards Walpole *''[[geographic coordinates|Coordinates]]'': {{coord|35|1|32.41|S|117|14|7.24|E|region:AU}}
