{{Italic title}}
'''''Sarasammana Samadhi''''' (Kannada: ಸರಸಮ್ಮನ ಸಮಾಧಿ) is a [[Kannada language|Kannada]] novel written by [[K. Shivaram Karanth]]. Through this novel Karanth gave a narrative of the Sati system and the social laws surrounding the marriage.<ref>{{cite book|title=Scholar Critic|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RodkAAAAMAAJ|year=1987|publisher=s.n.|page=103}}</ref><ref name="Karanth1993">{{cite book|author=Kota Shivarama Karanth|title=Ten Faces of a Crazy Mind: Autobiography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P1kOAAAAYAAJ|date=1 January 1993|publisher=Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan|isbn=978-81-7276-023-6}}</ref> For this novel Karanth won a [[Sahitya Akademi Award]].<ref name="Different angles">{{cite news|last1=Chowdhary|first1=Y. Sunita|last2=Chowdhary|first2=Y. Sunita|title=Different angles|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/different-angles/article2581032.ece|accessdate=22 March 2018|work=The Hindu|date=30 October 2011|language=en-IN}}</ref>

