{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Azerbaijan | country_link = Azerbaijan | continent = Asia | map_image = Azerbaijan with Nagorno Karabakh region.svg | map_caption = Location of Azerbaijan (green) and [[Republic of Artsakh]] (light green) | map_size = 200px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +994 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = 8 | regulator = | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | dial_plan_type = closed | number_format = | codes_list = }} '''Telephone numbers in [[Azerbaijan]]''' follow the [[ITU-T|ITU Telecommunication Standardization Sector]] [[E.164]] recommended format its [[telephone numbering plan]].
A caller from outside Azerbaijan would dial the international access number ([[international call prefix]]) of the originating country (00 for many countries, 011 from [[NANP]] areas), then dial the [[country code]] (in this case 994), omit the trunk prefix, then dial the two-digit area code, and then the seven-digit local number.
For example, to reach the US embassy in [[Baku]], Azerbaijan, a caller in the United States would dial 011 994 12 4980335, while a caller in the UK would dial 00 994 12 4980335. (The area code for Baku is 12.)
For calls within Azerbaijan but outside the caller's area code, the caller would not dial an international access number or country code, but dial the trunk prefix (in this case 8) then the area code, followed by the telephone number. So, for instance, to call the American embassy in Baku from [[Ganja, Azerbaijan]], a caller would dial 8 12 4980335.
For a local call (that is, a call in Azerbaijan within the caller's area code) one simply dials the local number: 4980335.
==Area codes in Azerbaijan== On August 1, 2011, Azerbaijan reorganized its national numbering plan for area codes.<ref>[http://www.itu.int/dms_pub/itu-t/oth/02/02/T020200000F0001PDFE.pdf "ITU Operational Bulletin No.986"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160221205951/http://www.itu.int/dms_pub/itu-t/oth/02/02/T020200000F0001PDFE.pdf |date=2016-02-21 }}, [[International Telecommunication Union]], Aug. 15, 2011.</ref> Only the area codes of Baku, [[Sumqayit]], and the [[Nakhchivan Autonomous Republic]] (area codes 12, 18 and 36) remain unchanged. The following tables list both the old and new area codes.
'''''Baku''''' {| class="wikitable" border="1" cellpadding="2" !Locality !Old area code !New area code |- |[[Baku]] |align="center"|12 |align="center"|12 |}
